learning_outcomes.en:
A student will:
Know the importance of the preanalytical phase to assure quality of laboratory tests;
Know how to prepare patients for clinical chemistry and hematology blood tests, while taking into account the patient status (age, elderly, pregnancy);
Know how to draw blood samples with the vacuum-technique;
Know how to assure POC testing quality;
Know how to take into account preanalytical factors and laboratory test quality when interpreting results
Know how to use knowledge of reference intervals and special conditions that apply to the elderly, children and pregnant women when interpreting laboratory test results.
